Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Boil the @Jasmine Rice{150%g}, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain, pop back in the #pan{} and cover.

Once hot, fry the @Diced British Chicken Thigh{260%g}, @Sliced Mushrooms{80%g} and @Mangetout{80%g}, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, cut the @Lime{1} into wedges.

Next, add the @Szechuan Paste{56.25%g}, @Soy Sauce{15%ml}, @Ketjap Manis{25%g}, @Honey{1%tbsp} and @Water{2%tbsp}.

Bring to the boil and stir. Lower the heat, then simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Taste and season. Add a splash of @?Water{} if needed.

Divide the rice and stir-fry between #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the @Salted Peanuts{25%g}.

Serve with the lime wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!